Usage
-----
"imageflow.js" has a function domReady (near the bottom) is the loader for the carousel.
Duplicate this in your html (after the include) to override the original.
You can then pass whatever params you need via your override.
NB: Dont use 'myImageFlow' again for the id!

Example
-------
domReady(function(){
	var instanceOne = new ImageFlow();
	instanceOne.init({
		ImageFlowID:'myCarousel',
		reflectPath:'/js/imageflow/',								<--- Path from website base to php script
		imagePath:'/home/kim/dev/src/www/yii/glitzaratti.com/',		<--- Website base path
		circular:true});
	});

<div id="myCarousel" class="imageflow">
	<img src="/userdata/image/test/AB.jpg" longdesc="" width="500" height="500" alt="A Shoe" />
</div>

